                <head>No. 569.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Wallace</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 31, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 123.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 258, of the 31st ultimo,
                    relative to the petroleum concession, and in which you report that the
                    Government of Turkey declines responsibility for dues paid thereunder, has been
                    received and bad attentive consideration.</p>
                <pb facs="0951" n="881" xml:id="pg_881"/>
                <p>As the alleged non-liability of Turkey for the dues paid under the concession
                    admittedly rests on the right claimed by the Porte to make the concession
                    itself, and as this Government denies the rightfulness of the concession in
                    question, the United States cannot admit Turkey’s eon-liability to refund the
                    dues. Accordingly all statements of dues paid should be presented by you <hi
                        rend="italic">pro forma</hi> and refund asked.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
